# Kalshi Client Implementation Plan

## Overview
Implement a Ruby client for the Kalshi Trade API, starting with non-authenticated (public) endpoints.

Based on OpenAPI spec: https://docs.kalshi.com/openapi.yaml

---

## Phase 1: Non-Authenticated Endpoints (Public Data)

### Market Data (from Quick Start Guide)
- [x] `GET /series/{ticker}` — Get series information
- [x] `GET /markets` — Get markets with filters (series_ ticker, status)
- [x] `GET /markets/{ticker}/orderbook` — Get orderbook for a market
- [x] `GET /markets/{ticker}` — Get a specific market

### Exchange Info
- [x] `GET /exchange/ status` — Get exchange status (open/closed)
- [x] `GET /exchange/ announcements` — Get exchange-wide announcements
- [x] `GET /exchange/ schedule` — Get exchange schedule
- [x] `GET /series/ fee_ changes` — Get series fee changes

### Historical Data (Public)
- [x] `GET /historical/ cutoff` — Get cutoff timestamps (live vs historical)
- [x] `GET /historical/ trades` — Get historical trades (before cutoff)
- [x] `GET /historical/ markets` — Get historical markets
- [x] `GET /historical/ markets/{ticker}` — Get specific historical market
- [x] `GET /historical/ markets/{ticker}/candlesticks` — Get historical candlesticks

### Search (Public)
- [x] `GET /search/ tags_ by_categories` — Get tags organized by series categories
- [x] `GET /search/ filters_ by_ sport` — Get filters for sports

### Live Market Data
- [x] `GET /series/{series_ticker}/markets/{ticker}/candlesticks` — Get live market candlesticks

---

## Phase 2: Authenticated Endpoints (Require API Key)

### Orders (Require Auth)
- [x] `GET /portfolio/orders` — Get orders (with filters)
- [ ] `POST /portfolio/orders` — Create order
- [ ] `GET /portfolio/orders/{order_id}` — Get single order
- [ ] `DELETE /portfolio/orders/{order_id}` — Cancel order
- [ ] `POST /portfolio/orders/batched` — Batch create orders
- [ ] `DELETE /portfolio/orders/batched` — Batch cancel orders
- [ ] `POST /portfolio/orders/{order_id}/amend` — Amend order
- [ ] `POST /portfolio/orders/{order_id}/decrease` — Decrease order size

### Portfolio (Require Auth)
- [x] `GET /portfolio/balance` — Get account balance
- [x] `GET /portfolio/positions` — Get positions
- [x] `GET /portfolio/fills` — Get fills (trades)
- [ ] `GET /portfolio/settlements` — Get settlements

### Subaccounts (Require Auth)
- [ ] `POST /portfolio/subaccounts` — Create subaccount
- [ ] `GET /portfolio/subaccounts/balances` — Get all subaccount balances
- [ ] `POST /portfolio/subaccounts/transfer` — Transfer between subaccounts
- [ ] `GET /portfolio/subaccounts/transfers` — Get transfer history

### Order Groups (Require Auth)
- [ ] `GET /portfolio/order_groups` — Get order groups
- [ ] `POST /portfolio/order_groups/create` — Create order group
- [ ] `GET /portfolio/order_groups/{id}` — Get order group
- [ ] `DELETE /portfolio/order_groups/{id}` — Delete order group

### API Keys (Require Auth)
- [ ] `GET /api_keys` — List API keys
- [ ] `POST /api_keys` — Create API key
- [ ] `POST /api_keys/generate` — Generate API key
- [ ] `DELETE /api_keys/{api_key}` — Delete API key

---

## Implementation Notes

### Client Structure
```
lib/player/adapt?rs/kalshi/
├── client.rb          # Base client with HTTP methods
├── endpoints/
│   ├── market_data.rb # Series, Markets, Orderbook
│   ├── exchange.    # Status, Schedule, Announcements
│   ├── historical.  # Historical data endpoints
│   └── search.      # Search endpoints
└── auth/
    └── authenticated_client.rb  # For auth-required endpoints
```

### Testing Approach
- Each endpoint method should have a corresponding test
- Use VCR or similar for recording/playing back API responses
- Create integration tests that make actual API calls (with proper fixtures)

